result.execSummary:
The defendant David J Coleman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. David J Coleman is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • David J Coleman was found guilty of False Imprisonment [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • David J Coleman was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • David J Coleman was found guilty of False Imprisonment, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • David J Coleman was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • David J Coleman was found guilty of Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • David J Coleman was found guilty of Intimidate Victim/Use or Attempt Force, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.45(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
